<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — three structured phases</h2>
  <p class="sub">Not a choice — every student does every phase. Total 75 min across solo prep, pair rehearsal, and AI rehearsal.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have rehearsed at least 6 questions from the bank (one per category), can answer a question I haven't seen using my framework, and have identified the strongest objection to my exoplanet's habitability claim with a planned response.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">1</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Solo prep (20 min)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Pick one question from each of the 6 categories. Sketch a 1-sentence answer for each. Notice which categories felt natural (probably Clarification + Evidence) and which felt hard (probably Devil's-advocate + Implementation). The hard ones are where today's work pays off.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">2</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pair rehearsal (30 min)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">With a partner, swap defender / questioner roles. Partner picks 3 questions from the bank (their pick, not yours — that's the point). You answer each with timing: ≤30 seconds per response. Aim for <em>specific evidence</em> in each answer, not general "well, NASA says…". Switch roles. Both of you note where you stalled.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">3</div>
      <div class="choice-title">AI rehearsal (25 min)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Use the <a href="/ai-partners/defense-practice-partner/">Defense Practice Partner</a> for the categories your partner didn't cover — especially Devil's-advocate (peers can be reluctant to push hard, AI isn't). Ask for the toughest version of one question. Use the <a href="/ai-partners/the-skeptic/">Skeptic</a> if you want a sharper stress-test of your verdict itself. Document both exchanges.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

